CLIENT-SIDE FLOW: DOWNLOADING FILES

 * Receive a Response

   resp, err := http.Get("http://example.com/file.txt")
   if err != nil {
       // handle error
   }
   defer resp.Body.Close()


 * Serve the File

   Stream the response body to the client to allow for download or viewing.

   _, err := io.Copy(w, resp.Body)
   if err != nil {
       // handle error
   }


   Here, w is the http.ResponseWriter.

 * Provide a Link

